originalText.text: Long wait ever I was there for like over an hour before I got seen, wouldn't listen to all of my concerns, kept cutting me off when I was talking, test came back inconclusive and they told me that his brain is working fine and that was it, took a whole hour after the lady called me telling me that I should expect the phone call from him to call me about an update for the genetic test you can cover your food, I asked for a referral for a therapist for my son but wasn't given a phone number or address on the referral. I basically feel like we didn't get nothing accomplished but good to know he doesn't have any genetic problems.

originalText.text: Had an appointment scheduled for 11am and I rescheduled it for 10am. When I arrived at the clinic and told the front desk person I had an appointment for 10am all she said was “I know.” After waiting 25 minutes, I approached the desk again and asked about my appointment. That is when she actually checked the time and updated me about a confusion in the system. Something that EASILY could’ve been solved immediately was put on hold because the receptionist was chatting on a personal call. Very frustrating.

originalText.text: Disorganized and uncaring. I arrived for a scheduled procedure only to be told that although the technician was there, the work couldn't be done because no doctor was present. They had not bothered to call and reschedule me, they just let me waste my time coming in for nothing. The technician was sitting in his room on his cellphone (if he can't work with no doctor present, why is he there?). This technician had done a previous procedure on me prior to this (a doctor was in the office that day) but I have never been given any analysis or results. I asked for the doctor to call me and was told that he would - he never has. Highly unprofessional.
